Privacy Policy for Pixel AutoStamp<br>

Effective Date: June 2, 2026
App Name: Pixel AutoStamp
Developer: IQ-Soft
Contact Email: iqsoft.support@gmail.com

1. Introduction

Pixel AutoStamp is a photo stamping application that automatically detects new photos taken on your Android device and creates a stamped copy of those photos based on the app’s configured settings.

This Privacy Policy explains how Pixel AutoStamp handles photos, files, permissions, and user/device data.

2. Data We Collect

Pixel AutoStamp is designed to work locally on your device.

The app does not collect, upload, sell, or share personal data with any external server, cloud service, analytics platform, or advertising network.

The app may access the following data locally on your device only:

Data / Permission	Purpose
Photos and images	To detect newly taken photos and create stamped copies
Media storage access	To read source photos and save stamped copies
Notification permission, if used	To notify the user when photos are detected or stamping is completed
Background processing permission, if used	To detect and process new photos after they are saved
App settings	To remember stamping preferences such as date, time, location text, or watermark style
3. How We Use Data

Pixel AutoStamp uses local device data only for the following purposes:

Detecting new photos saved by the device camera
Creating a stamped copy of each selected or detected photo
Saving the stamped copy on the device
Showing local notifications about stamping activity
Maintaining user-selected app preferences

The original photo remains unchanged. Pixel AutoStamp creates a separate stamped copy.

4. Photo Handling

Pixel AutoStamp may read photos from your device only for stamping purposes.

Photos are processed locally on the device. Photos are not uploaded to any server. Photos are not shared with the developer or any third party.

5. Data Sharing

Pixel AutoStamp does not share user data with third parties.

The app does not use:

Cloud upload
External servers
Analytics SDKs
Advertising SDKs
Third-party tracking
User profiling
Account creation or login
6. Children’s Privacy

Pixel AutoStamp is not specifically directed at children under the age of 13.

If the app is made available to children or selected as including children in the Google Play target audience, the app will be operated in compliance with applicable children’s privacy requirements and Google Play Families policies. Google Play states that apps including children in their target audience must comply with Families Policy requirements, and apps for children have additional limits on identifiers and data transmission.

7. Permissions

Pixel AutoStamp requests only the permissions required for its core functionality. Depending on Android version and app configuration, these may include access to photos/media, storage, notifications, and background processing.

Permissions are used only to support local photo detection and stamping.

8. Data Retention

Pixel AutoStamp does not store user data on external servers.

Stamped photos are saved locally on the user’s device. Users can delete stamped photos at any time using the app, gallery, or file manager, depending on device settings.

App preferences may remain stored locally until the user clears app data or uninstalls the app.

9. Security

Pixel AutoStamp is designed to process photos locally on the device. Since the app does not upload photos or user data to external servers, the risk of server-side exposure is reduced.

Users should still protect their device using standard Android security features such as screen lock, operating system updates, and trusted app sources.

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any updates will be posted on the same privacy policy page with a revised effective date.

11. Contact

For questions about this Privacy Policy or Pixel AutoStamp, contact:

Email:  iqsoft.support@gmail.com
